1.1 Installing APL
==================

APL is built and installed like this:

   тАв download the tar file containing GNU APL, from
     <ftp://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/apl> or from one of its mirrors (see
     <http://www.gnu.org/prep/ftp.html>), and un-tar the file.

   тАв read (and follow) the instructions given in file README in the
     unpacked directory.

   For the experienced, but impatient reader: it is the well-known
sequence

     $ ./configure [configure-option]...
     $ make
     $ sudo make install

   On success, make produces an executable filee named apl in
sub-directory src while make install installs that file (in
/usr/local/bin) as well as some other files in other locations (that can
be controlled via configure-options).

   File README contains further instructions about the installation GNU
APL.


