2.1.6 Helpful Features for Scripting
------------------------------------

GNU APL provides three system variables and functions that are
particularly useful for scripting:

   тАв тОХARG: access to the command line arguments given to the
     interpreter,
   тАв тОХENV: access to the environment variables of the process running
     the interpreter, and
   тАв тОХINP: Here-Document-alike function for creating large text
     variables

* Menu:

* тОХARG::
* тОХENV::
* тОХINP::


