2.20 Bit-wise Logical Functions тКдтИз, тКдтИи, тКдтН▓, тКдтН▒, тКдтЙа, and тКд=
==========================================================

The APL functions And (тИз), Or (тИи), Nand (тН▓), and Nor (тН▒) operate
primarily on Boolean integers.  Primarily means that the LCM variant for
тИз and the GCD variant for тИи are not considered in this context.  (The
LCM and GCD variants are defined in the ISO standard and supported in
GNU APL but not in IBM APL2).

   However, probably more often than not one needs to compute Boolean
functions between the bits of arbitrary (non-Boolean) integers and not
between entire Boolean integers 0 or 1.  Although that is possible to do
in standard APL, the procedure is fairly awkward and, more importantly,
inefficient:

   тАв convert every integer argument X to a 64-item Boolean vector
     XтЖР(64тН┤2)тКдX,
   тАв call the Boolean function тИз, тИи, тН▓, тН▒, =, or тЙа with the converted
     arguments, and
   тАв convert the Boolean result vector R back to the integer result
     ZтЖР2тКеR

   Note: for Boolean arguments the APL functions тЙа and = can be used to
compute the more customary Boolean functions XOR and XNOR respectively.
In this context = and тЙа are treated as Boolean functions even though
they accept non-Boolean arguments,

   For example, using 5 тОХCR (4тН┤256)тКдX to display X in hex:

           5 тОХCR (4тН┤256)тКд   AтЖР$ABBADEAD
     ABBADEAD
           5 тОХCR (4тН┤256)тКд   BтЖР$00FF00FF
     00FF00FF

           5 тОХCR (4тН┤256)тКд   2тКе ((64тН┤2)тКдA) тИз (64тН┤2)тКдB
     00BA00AD

   With the bit-wise And (тКдтИз) the same can be achieved in a simpler
fashion and far more efficiently:

           тНЭ Traditional AND
           5 тОХCR (4тН┤256)тКд   AтЖР$ABBADEAD
     ABBADEAD
           5 тОХCR (4тН┤256)тКд   BтЖР$00FF00FF
     00FF00FF

           тНЭ bit-wise AND
           5 тОХCR (4тН┤256)тКд   A тКдтИз B
     00BA00AD

