2.23.1 тМ╣[1] and тМ╣[2] - QR Factorizations
----------------------------------------

ZтЖРтМ╣[1] B and ZтЖРтМ╣[2] B compute a QR factorization of the real or complex
matrix B. The results of ZтЖРтМ╣[1] B and ZтЖРтМ╣[2] B are conceptually
identical, while the algorithms used to compute the results differ.
Also, ZтЖРтМ╣[1] B always exist, while ZтЖРтМ╣[2] B requires libgsl to be
installed when GNU APL is compiled.

   The axis argument X is used to either clear near-0 matrix items to
exactly 0.0 during the computation (in Garry HelzerтАЩs algorithm), or
else to select a different algorithm for computing the factorization.
Set XтЖРтОХCT if unsure.

   The result Z is a triple (Q R Ri)тЖРZ with the following properties.
Let тН┤B=(M, N).

