2.23.2.4 тМ╣[7] B: Print Polynomial B
...................................

Let B тЖР bтВА bтВБ bтВВ ...  bтВЩ.  The standard interpretation of this vector B
in APL is that B is an element of a vector space over the field тДЭ or тДВ.
The elementary APL primitives +, -, ├Ч and ├╖, but also the more powerful
primitives +.├Ч and тМ╣, and last but not least the scalar extension
mechanism of several primitive are tailored for this interpretation.

   However, another and less common interpretation of B is this: vector
B is a polynomial of (a single) indeterminant X:

   B тЖРтЖТ bтВА + bтВБX + bтВВX┬▓ + ...  + bтВЩXтБ┐

   This interpretation easily extends to APL values of higher rank, i.e.
matrices are polynomials of two indeterminants X and Y, values of rank 3
are polynomials of three indeterminants X, Y, and Z, and so on.  In this
case, assuming тОХIOтЖР0:

   тАв An APL value P with rank rтЖРтН┤тН┤P represents a polynomial with r
     indeterminants.
   тАв The item P[k;m;n;...]  is the coefficient of the polynomial term
     that has the indeterminant powers Xс╡ПYс╡РZтБ┐...
   тАв The vector P[;0;0;...]  are the coefficients of the polynomial
     terms with only powers of X,
   тАв The vector P[0;;0;...]  are the coefficients of the polynomial
     terms with only powers of Y,
   тАв The vector P[0;0;;...]  are the coefficients of the polynomial
     terms with only powers of Z,
   тАв and so on.  The other items of P are coeffiecients of the
     polynomial terms with mixed powers of the different indeterminants.
   тАв The item P[[0;0;0;...  aka.  тЖСP is the constant term of the
     polinomial.

   Function тМ╣[7] B, aka.  тМ╣.poly_print B returns a string with this
interpretation.  In its monadic form тМ╣[7] B it uses the names x, y, z,
...  for the indeterminants of the polynomial.  In its dyadic form A
тМ╣[7] B does iA specify the names that shall be used.  Two forms are
supported for A: the characters of a plain APL string (тН┤A == тН┤тН┤B) is
understood as a list of single character indeterminants.  iAlternatively
A list of nested strings A (again with (тН┤A == тН┤тН┤B)) is understood as N
different indeterminant names.  For example:

           тНЭ monadic, 1 indeterminant
           тМ╣.poly_print тОХтЖРPOLYтЖР3 2 1
     3 2 1
     x┬▓ + 2x + 3

           тНЭ monadic, 2 indeterminants
           тМ╣.poly_print тОХтЖРPOLYтЖР2 3тН┤тН│6
     1 2 3
     4 5 6
     6x┬▓y + 5xy + 4y + 3x┬▓ + 2x + 1

           тНЭ monadic, 3 indeterminants
           тМ╣.poly_print тОХтЖРPOLYтЖР3 3тН┤тН│9
     1 2 3
     4 5 6
     7 8 9
     9x┬▓y┬▓ + 8xy┬▓ + 7y┬▓ + 6x┬▓y + 5xy + 4y + 3x┬▓ + 2x + 1

           тНЭ dyadic, two 1-character indeterminants X and Y
           'XY' тМ╣.poly_print тОХтЖРPOLYтЖР2 3тН┤тН│6
     1 2 3
     4 5 6
     6X┬▓Y + 5XY + 4Y + 3X┬▓ + 2X + 1

           тНЭ dyadic, two named indeterminants _Foo and _Bar
           '_Foo' '_Bar' тМ╣.poly_print тОХтЖРPOLYтЖР2 3тН┤тН│6
     1 2 3
     4 5 6
     6_Foo┬▓_Bar + 5_Foo_Bar + 4_Bar + 3_Foo┬▓ + 2_Foo + 1



