2.23.2.5 A тМ╣[8] B: Multiply Polynomials A and B
...............................................

The scalar APL primitives + and - can be used for vectors and for
polynomials alike.  In contrast, the multiplication of two polynomials A
and B is different from the scalar multiplication A├ЧB and is also
different from the vector multiplication A +.├Ч B.

   Dyadic A тМ╣[8] B aka.  A тМ╣.poly_multiply B fills this gap and computes
the product of two polynomials.  For example:

           тНЭ single indeterminant x
           тНЭ
           "A:"    (тМ╣.poly_print A тЖР 4 0 0 6 3 1)
      A: xтБ╡ + 3xтБ┤ + 6x┬│ + 4

           "B:"    (тМ╣.poly_print B тЖР 5 0 2)
      B: 2x┬▓ + 5

           "PROD:" (тМ╣.poly_print PROD тЖР A тМ╣.poly_multiply B)
      PROD: 2xтБ╖ + 6xтБ╢ + 17xтБ╡ + 15xтБ┤ + 30x┬│ + 8x┬▓ + 20

           тНЭ two indeterminants x and y
           тНЭ
           "A:"    (тМ╣.poly_print A тЖР 2 2тН┤0 1 1 0)
      A: x + y

           "B:"    (тМ╣.poly_print B тЖР 2 2тН┤0 ┬п1 1 0)
      B: x - y

           "PROD:" (тМ╣.poly_print PROD тЖР A тМ╣.poly_multiply B)
      PROD: x┬▓ - y┬▓


