2.24 тОХCC - Character Classes
============================

Some older APL interpreters (e.g.  APL68000) had system variables for
character classes, such as тОХD for digits 0..9 or тОХA for letters A..Z.
GNU APL provides a single system function тОХCC for that purpose.

* Menu:

* monadic тОХCC B: Return character class::
* dyadic A тОХCC B: Test character class::


File: apl.info,  Node: monadic тОХCC B: Return character class,  Next: dyadic A тОХCC B: Test character class,  Up: тОХCC - Character Classes

2.24.1 monadic тОХCC B: Return character class
--------------------------------------------

тОХCC B returns all characters of character class(es) B. If B is an
integer scalar then the result is a character vector, If B is an integer
vector then the result is a nested vector of integer vectors, with one
item per character class.

           тНЭ character class 1: digits (old тОХD)
           тНЭ
           тОХCC 1
     0123456789

           тНЭ character class 2: uppercase letters A..Z (old тОХA)
     ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ

           тНЭ character class 3: lowercase letters a..z
     abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz

           ...

           тНЭ Line drawing characters
           тОХCC 7
     тФМтФАтФмтФАтФРтХТтХРтХдтХРтХХ
     тФЬтФАтФ╝тФАтФдтХЮтХРтХктХРтХб
     тФФтФАтФ┤тФАтФШтХШтХРтХзтХРтХЫ
     тХУтФАтХетФАтХЦтХФтХРтХжтХРтХЧ
     тХЯтФАтХлтФАтХвтХатХРтХмтХРтХг
     тХЩтФАтХитФАтХЬтХЪтХРтХйтХРтХЭ

           тНЭ Some mathematical symbols
           тОХCC 8
     тО▓тОЫтОЮтОбтОдтОзтОл
     тО│тОЬтОЯтОвтОетОитОм
     тЖФтОЭтОатОгтОжтОотОо
     тДХтДдтДЪтДЭтДВтОйтОн

   A special case is тОХCC тНм (or тОХCC тН│0: it prints the available character
classes for тОХCC:

           тОХCC тНм
           тОХCC   1:  digits 0-9 (same as тОХCC 10)
           тОХCC   2:  uppercase characters A-Z (same as тОХCC 26)
           тОХCC   3:  lowercase characters a-z (same as тОХCC ┬п26)
           тОХCC   4:  ASCII characters (same as тОХCC 127)
           тОХCC   5:  superscripts ( ┬▓┬│┬╣╩▓с╡Пс╡Рс╡ЧтБ░тБ▒тБ┤тБ╡тБ╢тБ╖тБ╕тБ╣тБ║тБ╗тБ╝тБ╜тБ╛тБ┐ )
           тОХCC   6:  subscripts ( с╡втВАтВБтВВтВГтВДтВЕтВЖтВЗтВИтВЙтВКтВЛтВМтВНтВОтВЦтВШтВЩт▒╝ )
           тОХCC   7:  line drawing chatacters
           тОХCC   8:  octal digits 0-7
           тОХCC   9:  some mathematical symbols
           тОХCC  10:  decimal digits 0-9
           тОХCC  16:  UPPERCASE HEXADECIMAL DIGITS 0-9 A-F
           тОХCC ┬п16:  lowercase hexadecimal digits 0-9 A-F a-f
           тОХCC  17:  Hexadecimal Digits 0-9 A-F a-f
           тОХCC  26:  UPPERCASE CHARACTERS A-Z
           тОХCC ┬п26:  lowercase characters A-Z
           тОХCC  33:  base32 encoding (RFC 4648)
           тОХCC  48:  greek characters A-╬й ╬▒-╧Й
           тОХCC  52:  characters A-Z a-z
           тОХCC  65:  base64 encoding (RFC 4648)
           тОХCC  95:  printable characters 0x20 ... 0x7E
           тОХCC 128:  ASCII characters

   In many cases is the character class number easy to remember because:

   тАв the character class number is equal to the number of characters in
     the class, e.g.  26 for A-Z, 52 for A-Z and a-z,
   тАв negative numbers are the lowercase variants of the uppercase class,
     e.g.  26 for A-Z and ┬п26 for a-z, and
   тАв 2*class is the mixed case of the uppercase class.


