   And thatтАЩs it: call тОХDLX to get the solution(s).  In general all
problems that can be solved by тОХDLX contain 3 steps:

   тАв translate the problem into a constraints matrix B,
   тАв ZтЖРтОХDLX B, and
   тАв translate the result Z back into the problem domain.

   Another application of тОХDLX is solving sudokus.  The constraints
matrix is a little more complicated, but the principle is the same.  GNU
APL is shipped with two workspaces: sudoku.apl (which solves sudokus
without using тОХDLX) and sudoku_DLX.apl (which solves sudokus using
тОХDLX).


