2.31 тОХFFT - Fast Fourier Transform
==================================

For those interested in signal processing and the like, GNU APL provides
тОХFFT:

   The monadic form тОХFFT B is a shortcut for the dyadic form 0 тОХFFT B.
It computes the FFT of complex or real B without applying a window
function.

   The dyadic form A тОХFFT B provides more control over what тОХFFT
computes.  A is an integer scalar which falls into one of three ranges.

   The first range from ┬п15 to ┬п10 does not compute an FFT, but returns
the result of multiplying B with one of several window functions, that
are frequently used in the context of FFTs.  The result has same shape
as B and can be used for analyzing or troubleshooting FFTs:

   тАв A=┬п10: no FFT, return the Hann window applied to B
   тАв A=┬п11: no FFT, return the Hamming window applied to B
   тАв A=┬п12: no FFT, return the Blackman window applied to B
   тАв A=┬п13: no FFT, return the Blackman-Harris window applied to B
   тАв A=┬п14: no FFT, return the Blackman-Nuttal window applied to B
   тАв A=┬п15: no FFT, return the Flat-Top window applied to B

   The second range around 0 contains the computation of the forward and
inverse FFTs:

   тАв 0 тОХFFT B returns the "normal" (aka.  forward) FFT of the numeric
     array B.
   тАв ┬п1 тОХFFT B returns the inverse FFT of the numeric array B.

   The third range from 10 to 15 corresponds to the first range and
first multiplies B with a window function and then computes the FFT:

   тАв A=10: FFT(B ├Ч Hann window)
   тАв A=11: FFT(B ├Ч Hamming window)
   тАв A=12: FFT(B ├Ч Blackman window)
   тАв A=13: FFT(B ├Ч Blackman-Harris window)
   тАв A=14: FFT(B ├Ч Blackman-Nuttal window)
   тАв A=15: FFT(B ├Ч Flat-Top window)

   тН┤тН┤B can be 1 (one-dimensional FFT, the most common case) or more.
The implementation of тОХFFT uses libfftw3, aka.  "The fastest Fourier
Transform in the West."  GNU APL checks the presence of libfftw3 when it
is ./configureтАЩd.  If libfftw3 is present then тОХFFT will hopefully
return the expected result; if not then a SYNTAX ERROR will be raised
when тОХFFT is used.

   тОХFFT honors the presence of /etc/fftw/wisdom (see man fftw-wisdom) to
speed up the computations performed by тОХFFT. Creating /etc/fftw/wisdom
will take a few hours, though, so that creating it will not pay off for
most mortals.


