2.33 тОХJSON - JSON Parsing
=========================

GNU APL provides тОХJSON for decoding and encoding JSON strings and files.
A (valid) JSON string is mapped to an APL value as follows:

   тАв JSON value тЖРтЖТ structured or non-structured APL value
   тАв JSON number тЖРтЖТ APL number
   тАв JSON string тЖРтЖТ APL string
   тАв JSON literal тЖРтЖТ enclosed APL string (one of either тКВтАЩnullтАЩ,
     тКВтАЩtrueтАЩ, or тКВтАЩfalseтАЩ )
   тАв JSON array тЖРтЖТ APL vector
   тАв JSON object тЖРтЖТ structured APL value (associative array)

* Menu:

* Monadic тОХJSON::
* Dyadic тОХJSON::


File: apl.info,  Node: Monadic тОХJSON,  Next: Dyadic тОХJSON,  Up: тОХJSON - JSON Parsing

2.33.1 Monadic тОХJSON
--------------------

ZтЖРтОХJSON B converts the string B into an APL value according to the
mapping above.  If that fails then command )MORE provides information
about the error and where in B the error was detected.


File: apl.info,  Node: Dyadic тОХJSON,  Prev: Monadic тОХJSON,  Up: тОХJSON - JSON Parsing

2.33.2 Dyadic тОХJSON
-------------------

ZтЖРA тОХJSON B performs one of the following conversions:

   тАв ZтЖР0 тОХJSON B is the same as monadic ZтЖРтОХJSON B.

   тАв ZтЖР1 тОХJSON B is like ZтЖР0 тОХXML B, except that B is not the JSON
     string itself but the name of a file from which a JSON string is
     read.

   тАв ZтЖР2 тОХJSON B is the inverse of ZтЖР0 тОХXML B. It converts an APL value
     to a JSON string.

   тАв ZтЖР3 тОХJSON B is like 2 тОХJSON B, except that the member names (keys)
     of all JSON objects are sorted alphabetically.  That is of little
     use (but costs performance) if Z is not displayed but processed
     further, but it could help troubleshooting when Z is displayed and
     the number of keys in Z is large.


