2.34 тОХMAP - Map Value
=====================

тОХMAP changes the ravel items of its right argument according to a
mapping table provided as its left argument.  Let ZтЖРA тОХMAP B.

   The left argument A of ZтЖРA тОХMAP B shall be a N├Ч2 matrix.  Each
2-element row of A, say A[J;], specifies a separate mapping A[J;1] тЖТ
A[J;2].  The result Z has the same shape as the right argument B. The
items Z[...]  of their result are constructed from their corresponding
items B[...]  in B as follows:

   тАв if B[...]  тЙб A[J;1] for some J then Z[...]  is A[J;2].

   тАв otherwise B[...]  is different from all A[1;J] and then Z[...]  is
     B[...]

   In other words, Z is B, but with items of B found in A[;1] replaced
by their mapped item A[;2].

   In practice the left argument A is frequently created from a literal
APL value such as 5 2тН┤тАЩeEwWaAzZ92тАЩ in the example below.  To simplify
these cases, A тОХMAP B also accepts a vector instead of a N├Ч2 matrix:

   A тОХMAP B тЖРтЖТ ((N 2)тН┤A) тОХMAP B if (2├ЧN) тЖРтЖТ тН┤A

   Examples:

           тНЭ the map A
           тКвAтЖР5 2тН┤'eEwWaAzZ92'
     eE    тНЭ map 'e' тЖТ 'E'
     wW    тНЭ map 'w' тЖТ 'W'
     aA    тНЭ map 'a' тЖТ 'A'
     zZ    тНЭ map 'z' тЖТ 'Z'
     92    тНЭ map '9' тЖТ '2'

           тНЭ the value B being mapped
           тКвBтЖР'Halloween'
     Halloween

           тНЭ the result of A тОХMAP B
           A тОХMAP B
     HAlloWEEn

           AтЖР'eEwWaAzZ92'   тНЭ vector A instead of N├Ч2 matrix
           A тОХMAP B
     HAlloWEEn

   NOTES:
   тАв The keys of the mapping A (i.e.  the elements in column A[;1]) must
     be unique.  If they are not then the mapping is ambiguous and a
     DOMAIN ERROR is raised.

   тАв Nested items in B: if an item of B is nested, then it is either
     equal to some (also nested) key, say A[N;1], (in that case it is
     being mapped to A[N;2] in the result), or it is different from all
     keys in A[;1] (and in that case the corresponding item in the
     result is the item in B.

   тАв Nested items in A: if a key, say A[N;1], is nested and matches an
     equal (hence also nested) item in B, then the corresponding item in
     the result will be A[N;2] (which may or may not be nested).  If a
     (nested or not nested) key A[N;1] is equal to an item in B, then
     the corresponding item in the result will be nested if A[N;2] is
     nested.  If, for some N, the depths of A[N;1] and A[N;2] differ,
     then depths of B and A тОХMAP B may differ as well.  That is, тОХMAP
     conserves the shape of B, but not necessarily the depth of B.

   тАв By default the mapping of B is non-recursive, i.e.  the top-level
     items of B are compared with the top-level keys A[;1], and nested
     keys and items of B are handled as described above.

     Sometimes, however, it is desirable to recursively descend into the
     nested sub-values of B (though never of A). This can be achieved by
     enclosing A as shown in the examples below.

           AтЖР5 2тН┤'eEwWaAzZ92'
           BтЖР'Hal' 'low' 'een'   тНЭ nested B
           4 тОХCR A тОХMAP B        тНЭ non-recursive (none of the keys in A[;1] matches)
     тФПтЖТтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФУ
     тФГтФПтЖТтФБтФБтФУ тФПтЖТтФБтФБтФУ тФПтЖТтФБтФБтФУтФГ
     тФГтФГHalтФГ тФГlowтФГ тФГeenтФГтФГ
     тФГтФЧтФБтФБтФБтФЫ тФЧтФБтФБтФБтФЫ тФЧтФБтФБтФБтФЫтФГ
     тФЧтИКтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФЫ

           4 тОХCR (тКВA) тОХMAP B   тНЭ recursive (some simple keys in A[;1] match)
     тФПтЖТтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФУ
     тФГтФПтЖТтФБтФБтФУ тФПтЖТтФБтФБтФУ тФПтЖТтФБтФБтФУтФГ
     тФГтФГHAlтФГ тФГloWтФГ тФГEEnтФГтФГ
     тФГтФЧтФБтФБтФБтФЫ тФЧтФБтФБтФБтФЫ тФЧтФБтФБтФБтФЫтФГ
     тФЧтИКтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФБтФЫ


