2.35.4 Eigenvector
------------------

The eigenvector operation, тОХMX[4], is monadic and returns the complex
eigenvectors of real non-symetric square matrices:

           B
     ┬п1  1 ┬п1 1
     ┬п8  4 ┬п2 1
     27  9  3 1
     64 16  4 1
           тОХPPтЖР4
           тОХMX[4] B
       0.09988            0.1113          ┬п0.2925          ┬п0.9445
       0.04308J0.009687  ┬п0.07091J0.1389   0.5166J┬п0.01601  0.8396J0.04139
       0.04308J┬п0.009687 ┬п0.07091J┬п0.1389  0.5166J0.01601   0.8396J┬п0.04139
      ┬п0.1449             0.3566           0.9194           0.08118

   where each row represents an eigenvector:

           EтЖРтОХMX[4] B
           E[тОХIO;]                   тНЭ first vector
     0.09988 0.1113 ┬п0.2925 ┬п0.9445
           E[тОХIO+1;]                 тНЭ second vector
     0.04308J0.009687 ┬п0.07091J0.1389 0.5166J┬п0.01601 0.8396J0.04139
           etc.

   The eigenvalues are computed concurrently and the eignenvector matrix
is sorted according to the descending magnitude of the corresponding
eigenvalues.


