2.35.5 Eigenvalue
-----------------

The eigenvalue operation, тОХMX[5], is also monadic with an argument of
the same shape as that of the argument of the eigenvector operation.  It
returns a sorted complex vector of eigenvalues of the matrix argument:

           тКвFтЖРтОХMX[5] B
     ┬п6.414 5.546J3.085 5.546J┬п3.085 2.323

   The order of eigen vectors, E from above, is related to the order of
the eigenvalues, F, by the relationship:

                  E[k;] тмД F[k]

   (Note that, from the above example:

           |F
     6.41391 6.346285607 6.346285607 2.3228

   the order of the magnitude of the elements is descending, making the
initial eigenvector, E[тОХIO;], the dominant eigenvector and each
successive eigenvector successively less significant.)

   Accordingly:

           4 тОХCR (тКВтНЙ(1,тН┤F)тН┤F),(тКВE)
