2.37.2 Monadic тОХPNG
-------------------

Monadic тОХPNG, i.e.  тОХPNG B is used for 3 purposes:

  1. Conversion of PNG files into the GNU APL color model,
  2. Display of an APL array (in the GNU APL color model) in a window on
     the screen (interactive use of PNG), and
  3. Controlling of тОХPNG itself.

   The desired purpose is dictated by the properties of *B*:

  1. Any APL text vector (i.e.  a string) *B* is taken as the name of a
     file that supposedly contains an image in the PNG format.  тОХPNG
     will read the file and return the pixels in it as a numeric APL
     array of rank 3.  The array contains the color components of the
     image in the file as described above.
  2. Any array *B* with rank 3 must be numeric (with values from 0.0 to
     1.0) and is then assumed to be an array in the GNU APL color model
     (such as the result of the case above).  This image is displayed in
     a new window on the screen; the window survives even after тОХPNG has
     returned.  The result returned by тОХPNG is a window handle (a
     positive integer identifying the window) which may later be used
     (in the case described below) to close the window programmatically
     from APL. Alternatively the window can also be closed interactively
     by the user via its close button.
  3. Finally, if *B* is a numeric scalar it fine-tunes the тОХPNG
     behaviour:

        тАв тОХPNG N with N тЙе 1 (as returned in the case above) closes the
          window with handle N programmatically.

        тАв тОХPNG 0 disables all debug printouts related to тОХPNG.
        тАв тОХPNG ┬п1 turns on a debug printout related to тОХPNG (X events).
        тАв тОХPNG ┬п2 turns on a debug printout related to тОХPNG (image
          data).
        тАв тОХPNG ┬п3 closes all open тОХPNG windows.
        тАв тОХPNG ┬п4 turns on a debug printout related to тОХPNG (GTK
          drawing).
        тАв тОХPNG ┬п5 turns on a debug printout related to тОХPNG (function
          calls).
        тАв тОХPNG ┬п6 returns a vector of all open тОХPNG window handles.


File: apl.info,  Node: Dyadic тОХPNG,  Next: APL Examples,  Prev: Monadic тОХPNG,  Up: тОХPNG - Portable Network Graphics

2.37.3 Dyadic тОХPNG
------------------

Dyadic *A тОХPNG B* has only one purpose: to store an APL array in the GNU
APL color model into a PNG file.

   тАв If *A* is a text vector then it is taken as the name of a PNG file
     into which the image *B* shall be written.  In this case the
     resolution is 8 bits for each color component.
   тАв If *A* is a 2-element vector, say *(A1 A2) тЖР A*, then the nested
     *A1* is the name of a PNG file as before and *A2* is the resolution
     (1, 2, 4, 8, or 16) to be used for the output file.  In this case
     the combination of the general image format (as implied by *тЖСтН┤B*)
     and resolution *A2* must be a valid one in the PNG standard.


