2.38 тОХPS - Print Style
======================

тОХPS is an integer vector that currently (read: as of SVN 982) contains
two integers which control some details of how APL values are printed.
The default value of тОХPS is 0 0.  тОХPS is a session variable which
survives the *)LOAD*ing of workspaces.

   тОХPS[1] = 0: print rational quotients as normal floating point numbers
(digits, fractional point, possibly an exponent).

   тОХPS[1] = 1: print rational quotients as Numerator├╖Denominator.

   Note: тОХPS[1] has no effect if rational numbers were not
./configureтАЩd.

   тОХPS[2] = 0: no "boxing" of APL values

   тОХPS[2] > 0: "boxing" of APL values according to тОХPS[2].

   Setting тОХPS[2] has the same effect as the debug command ]BOXING and
uses the same values.

   Note: For compatibility with older workspaces, assigning a single
value to тОХPS assigns that value to тОХPS[2] and sets тОХPS[1] to 0.


