2.39.5.4 the тОХRE error flag E
.............................

The default behavior of тОХRE is to return an empty result if no match of
the regular expression A is found in B. It is sometimes more convenient
to raise an error if no match is found.  This can be achieved with the E
flag:

            4 тОХCR 'g..' тОХRE[''] '__foo___fun____fox'
     тФПтКЦтФУ
     тФГ0тФГ
     тФЧтФБтФЫ
            'g..' тОХRE['E'] '__foo___fun____fox'
     DOMAIN ERROR+
           'g..' тОХRE['E']'__foo___fun____fox'
           ^            ^
           )MORE
     No match

   The тАЩEтАЩ flag has no effect if the тАЩgтАЩ flag is also given because in
that case it is natural to check the length of the result:

           4 тОХCR 'g..' тОХRE['Eg'] '__foo___fun____fox'
     тФПтКЦтФУ
     тФГ0тФГ
     тФЧтФБтФЫ


