2.42.1 тОХSQL[0] тНм : display sub-function numbers
-----------------------------------------------

The system function тОХSQL is divided into a number of sub-functions.  The
desired sub-function of тОХSQL is selected by means of a numeric axis
argument:

         Valid (sub-)function numbers for тОХSQL:

         Legend: Fs - database file name (path)
                 Ty - database type ('sqlite' or 'postgres')
                 Db - database handle (small integer)
                 Qs - SQL query string
                 Pv - query parameters (APL values, to be bound to Qs)
                 Ts - name of a table in the database (string)
                 Vi - DB provider (library) version (integer)
                 Vs - DB provider (library) version (string)

                 тОХSQL[0] ''        list the тОХSQL (sub-)function names
                 тОХSQL[0] тНм         list the тОХSQL (sub-)function numbers
         Db тЖР Ty тОХSQL[1] Fs        open database Fs & return a handle for it
                 тОХSQL[2] Db        close database handle Db
              Qs тОХSQL[3, Db] Pv    perform SQL query Qs
              Qs тОХSQL[4, Db] Pv    perform SQL update Qs
                 тОХSQL[5] Db        begin a transaction
                 тОХSQL[6] Db        commit the current transaction
                 тОХSQL[7] Db        roll the current transaction back
                 тОХSQL[8] Db        list the tables in database Db
              Db тОХSQL[9] Ts        list the column names and types of table Tn
         Vi тЖР    тОХSQL[10] Ty       the provider version number for type Ty
         Vs тЖР    тОХSQL[11] Ty       the provider version string for type Ty

   The axis argument [0] is optional; one can also use тОХSQL тНм.


