2.42.2 тОХSQL[0] тАШ''тАЩ : display sub-function names
------------------------------------------------

As of SVN version 1901, тОХSQL has been promoted to be a function group.
Instead of the function nunbers above, one can therefore also use
function names with the following syntax:

         With a small performance penalty, тОХSQL also accepts the following
         sub-function names instead of sub-function numbers as axis argument:

         Legend: Fs - database file name (path)
                 Ty - database type ('sqlite' or 'postgres')
                 Db - database handle (small integer)
                 Qs - SQL query string
                 Pv - query parameters (APL values, to be bound to Qs)
                 Ts - name of a table in the database (string)
                 Vi - DB provider (library) version (integer)
                 Vs - DB provider (library) version (string)

            тОХSQL[5]         тЖРтЖТ  тОХSQL.begin         тНЭ begin a transaction
            тОХSQL[9]         тЖРтЖТ  тОХSQL.columns       тНЭ show the columns of a table
            тОХSQL[6]         тЖРтЖТ  тОХSQL.commit        тНЭ end a transaction
            тОХSQL[2]         тЖРтЖТ  тОХSQL.close         тНЭ close a database handle
            тОХSQL[0]         тЖРтЖТ  тОХSQL.list ''       тНЭ тОХSQL function names/numbers
            тОХSQL[1] Fs      тЖРтЖТ  тОХSQL.open          тНЭ open the database file
            тОХSQL[3, Db] Pv  тЖРтЖТ  тОХSQL.query Db Pv   тНЭ SQL database query
            тОХSQL[7] Db      тЖРтЖТ  тОХSQL.rollback      тНЭ roll a transaction back
            тОХSQL[8] Db      тЖРтЖТ  тОХSQL.tables        тНЭ show all tables
         Qs тОХSQL[4, Db] Pv  тЖРтЖТ  тОХSQL.update Db Pv  тНЭ SQL database update
            тОХSQL[10]        тЖРтЖТ  тОХSQL.version       тНЭ SQL provider version number
            тОХSQL[11]        тЖРтЖТ  тОХSQL.vstring       тНЭ SQL provider version string

   NOTE: The mapping from function numbers to function names of a
function group does not allow for non-scalar axis arguments (such as [3,
Db]) for query or [4, Db] for update.  For that reason, the Db argument
of functions query and update had to be moved from the second item in
the axis argument to the first item of the right value argument, and the
right argument Pv (aka.  query parameters) of the function axis is now
the (nested) second argument of the right argument in the named function
symtax.

   Like for тОХSQL[0] тНм above is the axis argument [0] optional; one can
therefore also use тОХSQL тАЭ instead of тОХSQL[0] тАЭ.


