2.43.3 тОХSYL[24 25 26;]
----------------------

These system limits have been added in preparation for multi-core GNU
APL. They are currently not used.


File: apl.info,  Node: тОХSYL[27;],  Prev: тОХSYL[24 25 26;],  Up: тОХSYL - System limits

2.43.4 тОХSYL[27;]
----------------

This is not a limit that raises a limit error.  Instead it limits the
size of APL values when printed as statement results.  It is fairly easy
in APL to create huge APL values by mistake.  During development it can
be useful to limit the amount of data printed.  If the ravel length of,
say, VALUE exceeds тОХSYL[27;2] (i.e.  if тОХSYL[27;2] тЙд тН┤,VALUE) then
SHтЖСVALUE is printed instead of VALUE. The shape SH is computed like
this:

           SHтЖРтН┤VALUE
           while (ravel-length(SH) тЙе тОХSYL[27;2]) { divide longest axis in SH by 2 }


