2.44.6 XML Queries
------------------

The different functions in dyadic тОХXML are intended to construct XML
queries.  An XML query extracts information from, or modifies
information in, an XML document.  XML queries may differ considerably in
their details, but usually follow these top-level steps:

  1. Read an XML document into, say, APL (APLтЖР0 тОХXML B or APLтЖР1 тОХXML B)
  2. Optionally, display the structure of the document (3, 4, or 5 тОХXML
     APL)
  3. Select a subset of XML nodes (= GNU APL member names, 6 тОХXML APL)
  4. retrieve or modify the data in the selected XML nodes (with
     something like MEMBERSтЖР(тКВAPL) FUN┬и6тОХXML APLтЖРтОХXML followed by
     MEMBERтКГ )
  5. Optionally, convert the modified XML document back to XML (0 тОХXML
     APL)


