2.47 Monadic тЙа (Nub Sieve)
==========================

The nub sieve ZтЖРтЙаB of a value B is a Boolean vector Z with the same
shape as B and:

   Z[i] is 1 if B[i] is the first occurrence of B[i] in B and 0
otherwise.  For vectors B this can also be expressed as:

           тЙа B тЖРтЖТ (BтН│B)=(тН│тН┤B)

   Examples:

           тЙа'Hello, World.'
     1 1 1 0 1 1 1 1 0 1 0 1 1
           тЙа 1 (2 3) 4 (2 3) 5 6
     1 1 1 0 1 1


